title: Narrative Fill-ins and Q&A Multiple Choice
author: Wen

sentences.content: Scene narrative progressions let the user describe complex scenes by decomposing it into simpler subscenes.
Preparing food in the kitchen
The knives are stored in a wooden knife block.
A cutting board is protecting the counter.
A pair of shears are sitting on the counter.
Looks like a woman
The woman has short gray hair.
She is wearing a purple blouse.
She has a wedding band on her left ring finger.
Chopping vegetables
The woman is chopping carrots.
She will be chopping green onions and tomatoes next.
She seems to be chopping with her eyes closed.
